title._content: Writ of Habeas Corpus in the Case of U.S. ex. rel. John Wheeler v. Passmore Williamson, 7/19/1885

description._content: Title: Writ of Habeas Corpus in the Case of U.S. ex. rel. John Wheeler v. Passmore Williamson, 7/19/1885 From: Record Group/Collection: 21 Record Hierarchy Level: Item Scope and Content Note: This writ of habeas corpus commands Passmore Williamson to return Jane, Daniel and Isaiah, "persons of color." On the reverse side, Williamson responds that he does not have custody of these people Reference Unit: National Archives at Philadelphia Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=2641488 Repository Contact Information: NARA’s Mid Atlantic Region (Philadelphia) (NRBA), 900 Market Street, Philadelphia, PA, 19107-4292.
